amihttp.library/background                       amihttp.library/background

   PURPOSE

   amihttp.library is an AmigaOS HTTP/HTTPS client shared library for
   Amiga.  It wraps bsdsocket.library and amissl.library internally.  
   Applications hold only opaque handles; sockets, SSL contexts, connection 
   pools, and wire buffers are never exposed.

   BOOTSTRAP

   OpenLibrary(AMIHTTPNAME, AMIHTTPVERSION) is sufficient.  bsdsocket.library
   opens on first HTTP use; amisslmaster.library and OpenAmiSSLTags() run on
   first HTTPS use.  utility.library v47+ and dos.library v37+ are required
   at library open time.

   API TIERS

   Tier 0 — HttpBaseTagList / HttpError
     Per-process defaults (timeouts, pool limits, break mask).

   Tier 1 — HttpSession, HttpCookieJar
     Persistent client settings shared by many requests (User-Agent, proxy,
     redirect policy, optional cookie jar).

   Tier 2 — HttpTransaction  (primary API)
     Complete request/response cycle: wget, browser page load, REST, AJAX.
     HttpTransactionPerform sends the request and parses response headers.
     HttpTransactionReadBody streams the entity body in caller-supplied
     buffers.

   Tier 3 — HttpConnection
     Low-level streaming connection for WebDAV, custom protocols, or
     incremental wire I/O.  Simple GET/PUT should use Tier 2.

   TYPICAL TIER 2 FLOW

   HttpBase = OpenLibrary(AMIHTTPNAME, AMIHTTPVERSION);
   session = NewHttpSession();
   SetHttpSessionAttrs(session, HTSA_USERAGENT, (ULONG)"MyApp/1.0", TAG_DONE);
   txn = NewHttpTransaction(session);
   SetHttpTransactionAttrs(txn, HTTA_URL, (ULONG)url, HTTA_METHOD, (ULONG)"GET",
       TAG_DONE);
   HttpTransactionPerform(txn);
   status = HttpTransactionGetStatusCode(txn);
   while ((n = HttpTransactionReadBody(txn, buf, sizeof(buf))) > 0) {
       /* process buf[0..n-1] */
   }
   DisposeHttpTransaction(txn);
   DisposeHttpSession(session);
   CloseLibrary(HttpBase);

   ASYNC TIER 2 FLOW

   signal = AllocSignal(-1);
   SetHttpTransactionAttrs(txn,
       HTTA_NOTIFY_TASK,   (ULONG)FindTask(NULL),
       HTTA_NOTIFY_SIGNAL, signal,
       TAG_DONE);
   HttpTransactionPerformAsync(txn);
   while (!HttpTransactionIsComplete(txn))
       WaitHttpTransaction(txn, 1);
   FreeSignal(signal);
   /* then ReadBody loop as above */

   OWNERSHIP AND LIFETIME

   - DisposeHttpSession only after all child HttpTransaction and
     HttpConnection handles are disposed.
   - STRPTR values from HttpTransactionGetStatusLine(),
     HttpTransactionRespHeader(), HttpTransactionGetRedirectLocation(), and
     HttpTransactionRespHeaders() are library-owned until
     DisposeHttpTransaction().  Do not free them.
   - Tier 3 header accessors are valid until CloseHttpConnection().

   ERROR MODEL

   HttpTransactionGetLastError() and HttpError() report transport and
   protocol failures (ERROR_HTTP_*).  HttpTransactionGetStatusCode() reports
   the HTTP wire status (200, 404, 304, etc.).  A successful Perform with
   HTTP 404 is not a library error — check the status code separately.
   See amihttp.library/errors.

   REQUIREMENTS

   - AmigaOS 3.2 or 4.1.
   - bsdsocket.library (opened internally).
   - amisslmaster.library / AmiSSL for HTTPS (opened internally).
   - utility.library v47+, dos.library v37+.

   INCLUDE FILES

   #include <libraries/amihttp.h>
   #include <proto/amihttp.h>

   SEE ALSO
       amihttp.library/tags, amihttp.library/hooks, amihttp.library/errors,
       Examples/AGet.c, Examples/async_demo.c

amihttp.library/errors                           amihttp.library/errors

   GENERAL INFORMATION

   amihttp.library defines ERROR_HTTP_* codes in the 8700 range.  After any
   LVO returning FALSE/0, call HttpError() for the current error code.
   HttpGetErrorString(code) returns a static English description.
   HttpFault(code, header, buffer, len) formats a dos.library Fault()-style
   message into a caller buffer.

   CODES

   ERROR_HTTP_NOT_IMPLEMENTED (8700)
       Feature or LVO not yet implemented.

   ERROR_HTTP_DNS_FAILED (8701)
       Host name resolution failed.

   ERROR_HTTP_CONNECT_FAILED (8702)
       TCP connection failed.

   ERROR_HTTP_CONNECT_TIMEOUT (8703)
       Connect timed out.

   ERROR_HTTP_SSL_HANDSHAKE (8704)
       TLS handshake failed.

   ERROR_HTTP_SSL_VERIFY (8705)
       Certificate verification failed.

   ERROR_HTTP_READ_TIMEOUT (8706)
       Read timed out waiting for data.

   ERROR_HTTP_WRITE_FAILED (8707)
       Send failed on socket or SSL layer.

   ERROR_HTTP_READ_FAILED (8708)
       Read failed or unexpected EOF.

   ERROR_HTTP_ABORTED (8709)
       AbortHttpTransaction, break mask, or user cancel.

   ERROR_HTTP_PROTOCOL (8710)
       Malformed HTTP response.

   ERROR_HTTP_OUT_OF_MEMORY (8711)
       Memory allocation failed.

   ERROR_HTTP_INVALID_URL (8712)
       URL parse or composition error.

   ERROR_HTTP_INVALID_HANDLE (8713)
       Bad or disposed handle.

   ERROR_HTTP_PROXY_AUTH (8714)
       Proxy authentication required or failed.

   ERROR_HTTP_TOO_MANY_REDIRECTS (8715)
       Redirect limit exceeded.

   ERROR_HTTP_DECODE (8716)
       gzip/chunked decode error.

   SEE ALSO
       HttpError(), HttpGetErrorString(), HttpFault(), SetHttpError(),
       HTBT_ERRNOPTR

amihttp.library/hooks                             amihttp.library/hooks

   GENERAL INFORMATION

   Hooks are installed with SetHttpSessionHook() or SetHttpTransactionHook().
   Transaction hooks override session hooks for the same type.  The library
   dispatches hooks with utility.library CallHookPkt(hook, object, message).

   HOOK TYPES

   HTHK_PROGRESS (1)          — not yet invoked (reserved).
   HTHK_CERT_VERIFY (2)       — on TLS chain/hostname failure; see below.
   HTHK_REDIRECT (3)          — not yet invoked (reserved).
   HTHK_HEADERS_DONE (4)      — after response headers parsed.
   HTHK_BODY_CHUNK (5)        — after each HttpTransactionReadBody copy.
   HTHK_COMPLETE (6)          — after successful Perform (sync or async).
   HTHK_ERROR (7)             — on Perform failure.
   HTHK_LOG (8)               — not yet invoked (reserved).

   MESSAGE STRUCTURES

   HTHK_HEADERS_DONE — struct HttpHookHeadersDone
       hhd_Transaction, hhd_StatusCode

   HTHK_BODY_CHUNK — struct HttpHookBodyChunk
       hbc_Transaction, hbc_Data, hbc_Length
       hbc_Data points at the caller buffer passed to ReadBody for that call.

   HTHK_COMPLETE — struct HttpHookComplete
       hcp_Transaction, hcp_StatusCode, hcp_LastError

   HTHK_ERROR — struct HttpHookError
       her_Transaction, her_Code

   HTHK_CERT_VERIFY — struct HttpHookCertVerify
       hcv_Transaction, hcv_Cert (filled), hcv_VerifyResult (OpenSSL code),
       hcv_Accept (BOOL, set TRUE to trust peer).  Hook return non-zero or
       hcv_Accept TRUE overrides ERROR_HTTP_SSL_VERIFY for this connection.
       Install via SetHttpSessionHook(HTHK_CERT_VERIFY) or HTSA_SSL_CERT_HOOK.

   CERT VERIFY RETRY
       When verification fails without an accepting hook, Perform returns
       ERROR_HTTP_SSL_VERIFY.  Application flow:
       1) HttpTransactionGetPeerCert() for display/pinning UI.
       2) Install HTHK_CERT_VERIFY hook (or update HTSA_SSL_CERT_HOOK) that
          sets hcv_Accept TRUE for this certificate.
       3) Set HTTA_RETRY_CERT_VERIFY TRUE and call Perform again (one retry
          per transaction unless hook accepts on first failure).

   HTTA_POST_STREAM_HOOK — struct Hook *; message struct HttpHookPostStream.
       Hook return value = bytes copied into hps_Buffer (0 = error/EOF early).
       Pair with HTTA_POST_LENGTH and optional HTTA_CONTENT_TYPE.

   HTTA_FORM_MULTIPART — struct List * of HttpFormPart nodes.  Library builds
       multipart/form-data body before send; sets POST method when unset.

   PROXY
       HTSA_PROXY / HTBT_DEFAULT_PROXY: "host:port" or "http://host:port".
       Plain HTTP uses absolute URI in the request line.  HTTPS uses CONNECT
       tunnel then TLS to origin.  Proxy connections are never keep-alive
       pooled.  HTSA_PROXY_AUTH is encoded and sent on
       the first CONNECT/HTTP proxy request.  CONNECT 407 is retried once
       when proxy credentials are available (same as HTTP 407 status retry).

   PRE-EMPTIVE AUTH
       HTSA_CREDENTIALS sends Authorization: Basic on the first request.
       HTTA_RETRY_AUTH still enables a post-401 retry when needed.

   REDIRECTS
       301/302/303 switch to GET and drop body.  307/308 preserve method
       and request body (RFC 7231).

   SEE ALSO
       SetHttpSessionHook(), SetHttpTransactionHook(),
       <libraries/amihttp.h>

amihttp.library/tags                               amihttp.library/tags

   GENERAL INFORMATION

   TagItem-based configuration uses SetHttpSessionAttrsA(),
   SetHttpTransactionAttrsA(), and HttpBaseTagList().  Variadic wrappers
   HttpBaseTags(), SetHttpSessionAttrs(), and SetHttpTransactionAttrs() are
   provided in <proto/amihttp.h>.

   HTBT_* — HttpBaseTagList (Tier 0)

   HTBT_BREAKMASK
       Exec signal mask (e.g. SIGBREAKF_CTRL_C) polled during blocking
       HttpTransactionPerform and HttpTransactionReadBody.  Distinct from
       HTTA_NOTIFY_SIGNAL used for async completion.

   HTBT_ERRNOPTR
       Pointer to ULONG receiving a copy of HttpError() on failure.

   HTBT_DEFAULT_USERAGENT, HTBT_DEFAULT_PROXY, HTBT_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT
   HTBT_MAX_IDLE_CONNECTIONS, HTBT_IDLE_TIMEOUT, HTBT_SSL_VERIFY
       Process-wide defaults.  HTBT_SSL_VERIFY uses HTSSL_VERIFY_* values.

   HTBT_LOG_HOOK, HTBT_HTTP2_ENABLED — reserved for v2.

   HTSA_* — SetHttpSessionAttrsA (Tier 1)

   HTSA_USERAGENT, HTSA_PROXY, HTSA_PROXY_AUTH, HTSA_CREDENTIALS
   HTSA_MAX_REDIRECTS, HTSA_FOLLOW_REDIRECTS, HTSA_ACCEPT_ENCODING
   HTSA_KEEPALIVE, HTSA_MAX_CONNECTIONS
   HTSA_CONNECT_TIMEOUT, HTSA_READ_TIMEOUT, HTSA_TOTAL_TIMEOUT
   HTSA_SSL_CIPHER_LIST, HTSA_SSL_VERIFY, HTSA_SSL_CERT_HOOK
   HTSA_COOKIE_JAR, HTSA_TASK_SERIAL
       Task serial partitions the connection pool (stable ULONG, not task
       pointer).  HTSA_REFERER_POLICY: HTRP_NEVER, HTRP_ORIGIN, HTRP_ALWAYS.

   HTSA_PROXY_PAC_URL, HTSA_ALPN — reserved for v2.

   HTTA_* — SetHttpTransactionAttrsA (Tier 2)

   HTTA_URL, HTTA_BASE_URL, HTTA_METHOD
   HTTA_POST_BODY, HTTA_POST_LENGTH, HTTA_POST_STREAM_HOOK
   HTTA_RANGE_START, HTTA_RANGE_END
   HTTA_IF_MODIFIED_SINCE, HTTA_IF_NONE_MATCH
   HTTA_NO_CACHE, HTTA_NO_BODY, HTTA_FORM_MULTIPART
   HTTA_SOURCE_ADDRESS, HTTA_THROTTLE_BPS, HTTA_CHECKSUM
   HTTA_REFERER, HTTA_RETRY_AUTH, HTTA_USERAGENT
   HTTA_NOTIFY_TASK, HTTA_NOTIFY_SIGNAL
       Required for HttpTransactionPerformAsync.  Worker task signals
       notify task on completion.

   HTTR_* — HttpConnectionSendRequest (Tier 3, when implemented)

   HTTR_HOST, HTTR_HEADERS, HTTR_CONTENT_LENGTH, HTTR_CHUNKED, HTTR_USERAGENT

   SEE ALSO
       HttpBaseTagList(), SetHttpSessionAttrsA(), SetHttpTransactionAttrsA(),
       amihttp.library/background

amihttp.library/HttpBaseTagList                 amihttp.library/HttpBaseTagList

   NAME
       HttpBaseTagList -- Set per-process library defaults.  (V1)

   SYNOPSIS
       success = HttpBaseTagList(tags);
       D0                      A0

       LONG HttpBaseTagList(struct TagItem *tags);

       success = HttpBaseTags(Tag1, ...);

       LONG HttpBaseTags(ULONG, ...);

   FUNCTION
       Configures process-wide defaults after OpenLibrary().  Tags are
       HTBT_* values; see amihttp.library/tags.

   INPUTS
       tags - TagItem array terminated with TAG_DONE, or variadic TAG_DONE
           list for HttpBaseTags().

   RESULT
       success - TRUE (1) on success, FALSE (0) on failure.  Call HttpError()
           when FALSE.

   SEE ALSO
       HttpError(), amihttp.library/tags, HttpBaseTags()

amihttp.library/HttpBaseTags                       amihttp.library/HttpBaseTags

   NAME
       HttpBaseTags -- Variadic wrapper for HttpBaseTagList.  (V1)

   SYNOPSIS
       success = HttpBaseTags(Tag1, ...);

       LONG HttpBaseTags(ULONG, ...);

   FUNCTION
       Convenience wrapper around HttpBaseTagList().  Defined as a static
       inline in <proto/amihttp.h>.

   SEE ALSO
       HttpBaseTagList(), amihttp.library/tags

amihttp.library/HttpError                           amihttp.library/HttpError

   NAME
       HttpError -- Return current library error code.  (V1)

   SYNOPSIS
       code = HttpError();
       D0

       LONG HttpError(VOID);

   FUNCTION
       Returns the most recent ERROR_HTTP_* code for this process.  Cleared
       to 0 on successful LVO calls.  Use HTBT_ERRNOPTR to mirror errors to
       a caller-owned ULONG automatically.

   RESULT
       code - 0 if no error, otherwise ERROR_HTTP_* value.

   SEE ALSO
       SetHttpError(), HttpGetErrorString(), HttpFault(),
       amihttp.library/errors

amihttp.library/SetHttpError                     amihttp.library/SetHttpError

   NAME
       SetHttpError -- Set current library error code.  (V1)

   SYNOPSIS
       old = SetHttpError(code);
       D0               D0

       LONG SetHttpError(LONG code);

   FUNCTION
       Sets the library-wide error code (for example after application-level
       validation).  Returns the previous code.

   INPUTS
       code - new ERROR_HTTP_* value, or 0 to clear.

   RESULT
       old - previous error code.

   SEE ALSO
       HttpError()

amihttp.library/HttpGetErrorString         amihttp.library/HttpGetErrorString

   NAME
       HttpGetErrorString -- English text for an error code.  (V1)

   SYNOPSIS
       str = HttpGetErrorString(code);
       D0                     D0

       STRPTR HttpGetErrorString(LONG code);

   FUNCTION
       Returns a static string describing an ERROR_HTTP_* code.

