amihttp.library/HttpTransactionRespHeaders
                                      amihttp.library/HttpTransactionRespHeaders

   NAME
       HttpTransactionRespHeaders -- List of all response headers.  (V1)

   SYNOPSIS
       list = HttpTransactionRespHeaders(txn);
       D0                                  A0

       struct List *HttpTransactionRespHeaders(struct HttpTransaction *);

   FUNCTION
       Returns pointer to a struct List of struct HttpHeader nodes
       (hh_Name, hh_Value).  List is library-owned until dispose.

   INPUTS
       txn - HttpTransaction handle.

   RESULT
       list - struct List pointer, or NULL on bad handle.

   SEE ALSO
       HttpTransactionRespHeader(), <libraries/amihttp.h> struct HttpHeader

amihttp.library/HttpTransactionReadBody
                                      amihttp.library/HttpTransactionReadBody

   NAME
       HttpTransactionReadBody -- Stream response body bytes.  (V1)

   SYNOPSIS
       n = HttpTransactionReadBody(txn, buffer, buflen);
       D0                            A0   A1       D0

       LONG HttpTransactionReadBody(struct HttpTransaction *, APTR, ULONG);

   FUNCTION
       Copies up to buflen decoded body bytes into caller buffer.  Call in a
       loop until 0 is returned.  Chunked transfer and Content-Length clamping
       are handled internally.  gzip Content-Encoding returns
       ERROR_HTTP_NOT_IMPLEMENTED until decode is wired.

       Invokes HTHK_BODY_CHUNK hook after each successful copy.

   INPUTS
       txn    - HttpTransaction after Perform.
       buffer - destination buffer (caller allocated).
       buflen - size of buffer (capped internally to 8192).

   RESULT
       n - bytes copied (>0), or 0 at EOF or on failure (check HttpError()
           and HttpTransactionGetLastError()).

   NOTES
       Perform must complete before ReadBody.  For HEAD or HTTA_NO_BODY,
       ReadBody always returns 0.

   SEE ALSO
       HttpTransactionPerform(), HttpTransactionGetBytesReceived(),
       HttpTransactionGetContentLength()

amihttp.library/HttpTransactionGetRedirectLocation
                              amihttp.library/HttpTransactionGetRedirectLocation

   NAME
       HttpTransactionGetRedirectLocation -- Location header value.  (V1)

   SYNOPSIS
       url = HttpTransactionGetRedirectLocation(txn);
       D0                                       A0

       STRPTR HttpTransactionGetRedirectLocation(struct HttpTransaction *);

   FUNCTION
       Returns redirect URL from Location header when status is 3xx.
       Library-owned until DisposeHttpTransaction().

   INPUTS
       txn - HttpTransaction after Perform.

   RESULT
       url - STRPTR or NULL.

   SEE ALSO
       HttpTransactionGetStatusCode(), HTSA_FOLLOW_REDIRECTS

amihttp.library/HttpTransactionGetContentLength
                              amihttp.library/HttpTransactionGetContentLength

   NAME
