amihttp.library/OpenHttpConnection             amihttp.library/OpenHttpConnection

   NAME
       OpenHttpConnection -- Open Tier 3 streaming connection.  (V1)

   SYNOPSIS
       conn = OpenHttpConnection(session, host, port, ssl);
       D0                          A0       A1    D0    D1

       struct HttpConnection *OpenHttpConnection(struct HttpSession *,
           STRPTR host, ULONG port, BOOL ssl);

   FUNCTION
       Acquires pooled TCP or TLS connection to host:port.  port 0 selects
       default (80 or 443).  Caller sends raw bytes or uses higher-level
       helpers when implemented.

   INPUTS
       session - HttpSession handle.
       host    - hostname.
       port    - TCP port, or 0 for default.
       ssl     - TRUE for HTTPS.

   RESULT
       conn - HttpConnection handle, or NULL on failure.

   SEE ALSO
       CloseHttpConnection(), HttpConnectionReadResponseHeaders()

